    • Method Detail

      • readBlock

        int readBlock​(ByteBuffer buffer,
              long offset)
        Try to read a block of data into the provided buffer, starting with a given offset. Maximum number of bytes to be read is determined by Buffer.remaining().

        Storage must throw an exception if

        offset > capacity() - buffer.remaining()
        Parameters:
        buffer - Buffer to read bytes into. Value returned by buffer.remaining() determines the maximum number of bytes to read.
        offset - Index to start reading from (0-based)
        Returns:
        Actual number of bytes read
        Since:
        1.0

      • readBlock

        default int readBlock​(byte[] buffer,
                      long offset)
        Try to read a block of data into the provided array, starting with a given offset. Maximum number of bytes to be read is determined by Buffer.remaining().

        Storage must throw an exception if

        offset > capacity() - length
        Parameters:
        buffer - Array to read bytes into. Array's length determines the maximum number of bytes to read.
        offset - Index to starting reading from (0-based)
        Returns:
        Actual number of bytes read
        Since:
        1.0

      • writeBlock

        int writeBlock​(ByteBuffer buffer,
               long offset)
        Try to write a block of data from the provided buffer to this storage, starting with a given offset.

        Maximum number of bytes to be written is determined by Buffer.remaining().

        Storage must throw an exception if

        offset > capacity() - buffer.remaining()
        Parameters:
        buffer - Buffer containing the block of data to write to this storage. Value returned by buffer.remaining() determines the maximum number of bytes to write.
        offset - Offset in this storage's data to start writing to (0-based)
        Returns:
        Actual number of bytes written
        Since:
        1.0

      • writeBlock

        default int writeBlock​(byte[] block,
                       long offset)
        Try to write a block of data to this storage, starting with a given offset.

        Maximum number of bytes to be written is determined by block's length.

        Storage must throw an exception if

        offset > capacity() - block.length
        Parameters:
        block - Block of data to write to this storage. Block's length determines the maximum number of bytes to write.
        offset - Offset in this storage's data to start writing to (0-based)
        Returns:
        Actual number of bytes written
        Since:
        1.0
